explanation: This solution uses a stack to keep track of the characters in the string. It iterates through the string, and for each character, it checks if the top of the stack is the same character. If it is, it pops the top of the stack, effectively removing the closest occurrence of the character to the left. If it's not, it pushes the character onto the stack. The final length of the stack is the length of the minimized string.

